1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:04,973
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

3
00:00:04,973 --> 00:00:06,374
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

4
00:00:06,374 --> 00:00:07,442
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

5
00:00:13,032 --> 00:00:14,566
If he's watching me again today,

6
00:00:14,566 --> 00:00:16,068
he'll definitely come back.

7
00:00:17,269 --> 00:00:20,339
His goal must be to destroy
all the seedlings.

8
00:00:20,339 --> 00:00:22,808
So he'll definitely come back.

9
00:00:50,636 --> 00:00:52,738
Hey! Stop right there!

10
00:00:53,605 --> 00:00:55,307
I'll catch you no matter what!

11
00:00:55,507 --> 00:00:56,375
Stop right there!

12
00:00:56,909 --> 00:00:57,743
Hey.

13
00:01:42,388 --> 00:01:44,890
What are you doing here?

14
00:01:45,424 --> 00:01:47,092
Why are you running away?

15
00:01:48,827 --> 00:01:50,963
That Yeonri-ri branch manager
you mentioned...

16
00:01:50,963 --> 00:01:53,665
I looked into it, and officially...

17
00:01:54,366 --> 00:01:55,467
there is no manager.

18
00:01:56,769 --> 00:01:58,003
I confirmed with headquarters.

19
00:01:58,003 --> 00:01:59,972
There's no such management position
at the Yeonri-ri branch.

20
00:02:00,506 --> 00:02:02,207
Who in the world are you?

21
00:02:02,741 --> 00:02:04,877
You're the one who ruined
my field, aren't you?

22
00:02:04,877 --> 00:02:06,412
Did Mr. Choi send you?

23
00:02:06,412 --> 00:02:09,248
Let me make one thing clear.

24
00:02:09,848 --> 00:02:11,050
The one who ruined this field...

25
00:02:12,251 --> 00:02:13,285
wasn't me.

26
00:02:13,686 --> 00:02:16,522
Then why are you here at this hour?

27
00:02:17,489 --> 00:02:19,558
Because this field is important to me too.

28
00:02:23,295 --> 00:02:25,664
You're not even a manager
hired by Mat Story,

29
00:02:25,664 --> 00:02:27,599
so why would I believe you?

30
00:02:28,233 --> 00:02:30,636
Tell me the real reason.

31
00:02:32,705 --> 00:02:34,073
What's that in your hand?

32
00:02:34,073 --> 00:02:35,607
Give it here!

33
00:02:35,607 --> 00:02:37,076
- It's nothing.
- Give it!

34
00:02:37,076 --> 00:02:40,079
- Why are you doing this?
- Give it to me.

35
00:02:51,123 --> 00:02:52,057
This...

36
00:02:53,959 --> 00:02:56,028
You saw something, didn't you?

37
00:02:57,129 --> 00:02:58,964
You know something, don't you?

38
00:02:59,865 --> 00:03:00,766
I...

39
00:03:06,138 --> 00:03:10,275
(EP 6 I Thought I Knew Everything
Inside and Out)

40
00:03:18,283 --> 00:03:20,786
I can't see anything from here.

41
00:03:25,858 --> 00:03:27,993
This tiny thing looks like a person.

42
00:03:30,696 --> 00:03:32,664
What if it really is someone
from Yeonri-ri?

43
00:03:39,438 --> 00:03:41,907
It's like the ancestors are telling me
not to watch.

44
00:03:44,843 --> 00:03:46,078
They're not strangers.

45
00:03:46,712 --> 00:03:48,947
They're like family.
I can't be suspicious of them.

46
00:03:50,482 --> 00:03:51,750
I'll be punished for that.

47
00:04:10,969 --> 00:04:12,771
Mr. Choi isn't acting alone.

48
00:04:12,771 --> 00:04:14,506
(Executive Bae, order, Director Choi)

49
00:04:14,506 --> 00:04:17,342
The manager definitely knows something.

50
00:04:18,911 --> 00:04:19,745
This...

51
00:04:20,379 --> 00:04:21,747
You saw something, didn't you?

52
00:04:22,448 --> 00:04:24,316
You know something, don't you?

53
00:04:27,820 --> 00:04:29,254
I can't tell you anything.

54
00:04:30,522 --> 00:04:31,390
Do you have...

55
00:04:32,658 --> 00:04:34,660
any idea how desperate I am right now?

56
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:36,362
What kind of situation I'm in?

57
00:04:37,529 --> 00:04:38,997
If you'd just tell me...

58
00:04:38,997 --> 00:04:41,100
what you saw... Please...

59
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:42,735
Please tell me.

60
00:04:42,735 --> 00:04:43,635
I'm sorry.

61
00:04:45,471 --> 00:04:46,438
I can't make...

62
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:48,807
the same mistake twice.

63
00:04:52,711 --> 00:04:55,547
He said he can't make
the same mistake twice.

64
00:04:57,282 --> 00:04:59,151
Does that mean he did something wrong...

65
00:04:59,151 --> 00:05:01,487
to the villagers in Yeonri-ri before?

66
00:05:02,988 --> 00:05:03,822
Then...

67
00:05:04,823 --> 00:05:06,759
why is he still here?

68
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:07,893
And what's with this hairpin?

69
00:05:09,028 --> 00:05:10,763
If he tried to hide this hairpin,

70
00:05:10,763 --> 00:05:12,664
it means he was trying to cover
for someone.

71
00:05:14,566 --> 00:05:16,135
(List of suspects)

72
00:05:16,135 --> 00:05:18,237
Those who can wear that hairpin are...

73
00:05:24,376 --> 00:05:27,613
In the end, it comes back
to the Yeonri-ri villagers.

74
00:05:37,222 --> 00:05:39,158
Will he be home late again today?

75
00:05:40,759 --> 00:05:42,194
Should I call him?

76
00:05:46,732 --> 00:05:49,435
No. He's probably got a lot on his mind.

77
00:05:50,469 --> 00:05:53,138
I'll just let him do what he wants.

78
00:06:00,579 --> 00:06:01,847
Let's go to bed.

79
00:06:23,969 --> 00:06:25,003
Where are you?

80
00:06:26,472 --> 00:06:28,240
Pay me back, you wench.

81
00:06:34,413 --> 00:06:37,015
You thought I wouldn't find you?

82
00:06:38,617 --> 00:06:41,220
You thought hiding in some rural town
in Korea would keep me from finding you?

83
00:06:42,454 --> 00:06:43,756
Who...

84
00:06:43,756 --> 00:06:44,757
Who is it?

85
00:06:51,997 --> 00:06:53,232
Who is it?

86
00:07:06,145 --> 00:07:07,012
It's me.

87
00:07:08,514 --> 00:07:09,448
You scared me.

88
00:07:10,215 --> 00:07:14,053
What brings you here at this late hour?

89
00:07:14,053 --> 00:07:15,587
It's not that late.

90
00:07:16,755 --> 00:07:19,091
I... Anyway, come on in.

91
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:32,071
Here.

92
00:07:33,739 --> 00:07:34,773
I...

93
00:07:35,407 --> 00:07:36,875
brought this for you.

94
00:07:38,010 --> 00:07:40,412
What is it?

95
00:07:40,879 --> 00:07:42,414
Fresh kimchi.

96
00:07:43,315 --> 00:07:46,418
Ju Hyeong's cabbage was really sweet,

97
00:07:46,418 --> 00:07:47,886
so I thought you should try some.

98
00:07:48,687 --> 00:07:49,555
I see.

99
00:07:50,222 --> 00:07:52,725
All right. I'll get going now.

100
00:07:53,525 --> 00:07:55,127
Okay. Bye.

101
00:07:55,127 --> 00:07:56,862
Goodbye.

102
00:07:56,862 --> 00:07:57,863
Bye.

103
00:07:57,863 --> 00:07:59,665
Thank you.

104
00:07:59,665 --> 00:08:01,767
How sweet. Bye.

105
00:08:01,767 --> 00:08:02,668
Bye.

106
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:05,537
Bye.

107
00:08:10,442 --> 00:08:11,276
That scared me.

108
00:08:12,344 --> 00:08:14,480
I thought someone was actually
following me.

109
00:08:52,951 --> 00:08:54,853
Honey, I'm home.

110
00:08:54,853 --> 00:08:58,390
Can I get a glass of water too?
My head's pounding.

111
00:08:59,024 --> 00:09:00,225
Where's the painkiller?

112
00:09:02,594 --> 00:09:04,630
Medicine? Are you sick too?

113
00:09:06,231 --> 00:09:08,100
No, it's just sleeping pills.

114
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,768
Just sometimes...

115
00:09:09,768 --> 00:09:10,903
It's not anything strong.

116
00:09:10,903 --> 00:09:12,805
I occasionally take one
when I can't sleep.

117
00:09:13,839 --> 00:09:16,141
Because of the stress from raising kids,

118
00:09:16,141 --> 00:09:18,577
all moms take it.

119
00:09:19,878 --> 00:09:23,749
Right. You said you need something
for your headache, didn't you?

120
00:09:23,749 --> 00:09:25,984
Where is it? Hold on.

121
00:09:27,286 --> 00:09:28,120
Right.

122
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,955
Honey, are you really okay?

123
00:09:30,923 --> 00:09:32,458
Yes, I'm fine.

124
00:09:34,293 --> 00:09:36,061
It must've been tough in Canada.

125
00:09:37,296 --> 00:09:39,064
It couldn't have been easy.

126
00:09:44,703 --> 00:09:46,305
Hey, Wang Dong Sik.

127
00:09:46,305 --> 00:09:48,540
The door's open. Come in and eat.

128
00:09:57,116 --> 00:09:58,283
Chief.

129
00:09:59,251 --> 00:10:01,220
I came because I have something
to tell you.

130
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:02,955
What are you doing here
so early in the morning?

131
00:10:03,389 --> 00:10:06,191
The person who ruined my field...

132
00:10:06,191 --> 00:10:07,860
I think it's someone from this village.

133
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,629
You're still saying that?

134
00:10:10,629 --> 00:10:13,665
You've been running around
investigating it for days.

135
00:10:13,665 --> 00:10:14,967
Did you find any proof?

136
00:10:17,936 --> 00:10:18,804
Here.

137
00:10:21,073 --> 00:10:22,508
What's this?

138
00:10:24,376 --> 00:10:27,012
This was found in the field.

139
00:10:27,012 --> 00:10:28,480
Do you recognize whose it is?

140
00:10:30,282 --> 00:10:32,418
Do you know how many people
wear hairpins in this village?

141
00:10:33,152 --> 00:10:35,254
Why...

142
00:10:35,988 --> 00:10:37,589
are you getting so angry?

143
00:10:38,223 --> 00:10:39,124
You know something, don't you?

144
00:10:39,124 --> 00:10:41,593
You watched the camera footage,
didn't you?

145
00:10:42,861 --> 00:10:44,596
The camera footage is useless.

146
00:10:45,230 --> 00:10:46,098
What?

147
00:10:49,301 --> 00:10:51,470
It doesn't show who the culprit is.

148
00:10:53,272 --> 00:10:55,274
It does look like a human shadow, right?

149
00:10:56,175 --> 00:10:58,977
It's too far to tell if it's a person
or an animal.

150
00:10:59,878 --> 00:11:02,014
What animal stands on two legs?

151
00:11:02,514 --> 00:11:04,016
Kangaroos do.

152
00:11:05,517 --> 00:11:07,119
Deer do too.

153
00:11:07,119 --> 00:11:08,554
Boars do too.

154
00:11:09,288 --> 00:11:10,556
All animals stand on two legs
in Yeonri-ri.

155
00:11:12,124 --> 00:11:13,625
Are you really going to be like this?

156
00:11:13,625 --> 00:11:15,761
I'm shocked too, you know.

157
00:11:16,462 --> 00:11:19,732
I can't believe someone from Yeonri-ri
would do such a thing.

158
00:11:19,732 --> 00:11:20,999
I don't want to believe it.

159
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:22,868
If you don't want to believe it,

160
00:11:22,868 --> 00:11:25,137
then you just need to find
the real culprit.

161
00:11:25,137 --> 00:11:27,473
You and me together.

162
00:11:28,374 --> 00:11:29,408
Together?

163
00:11:29,408 --> 00:11:30,309
Yes.

164
00:11:31,110 --> 00:11:32,010
Together.

165
00:11:32,911 --> 00:11:33,879
Together.

166
00:11:34,613 --> 00:11:35,514
Together?

167
00:11:40,152 --> 00:11:42,621
(Where are you? Pay me back, you wench)

168
00:11:42,621 --> 00:11:45,491
I'm going crazy here.
What am I supposed to do?

169
00:11:59,171 --> 00:12:00,939
Should I try contacting Yeong Eun?

170
00:12:02,841 --> 00:12:03,742
No.

171
00:12:04,476 --> 00:12:06,078
She's in the U.S. too.

172
00:12:06,078 --> 00:12:08,347
It's not like she'd have money either.

173
00:12:09,948 --> 00:12:10,783
Pass.

174
00:12:12,151 --> 00:12:13,218
Then...

175
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:15,587
Ji Hye.

176
00:12:16,555 --> 00:12:18,724
Her husband's a judge.

177
00:12:19,892 --> 00:12:21,593
Maybe she can help me financially.

178
00:12:23,462 --> 00:12:26,198
No, we haven't talked in years.

179
00:12:26,198 --> 00:12:28,000
She probably wouldn't even answer my call.

180
00:12:31,437 --> 00:12:33,305
Should I just call my sister?

181
00:12:34,973 --> 00:12:36,575
No, I can't do that.

182
00:12:37,376 --> 00:12:38,777
If she finds out,

183
00:12:38,777 --> 00:12:41,680
it's only a matter of time before Tae Hun
and Mom find out too.

184
00:12:43,716 --> 00:12:45,184
I'm going crazy here.

185
00:12:47,119 --> 00:12:48,587
What am I going to do?

186
00:13:13,178 --> 00:13:14,079
Honey.

187
00:13:15,247 --> 00:13:16,215
I'm sorry.

188
00:13:17,950 --> 00:13:21,520
But it's better than stealing, right?

189
00:13:32,931 --> 00:13:34,933
I won't believe the culprit
is someone from Yeonri-ri,

190
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:36,668
no matter what.

191
00:13:37,069 --> 00:13:39,838
That's why I won't gather everyone here...

192
00:13:39,838 --> 00:13:42,141
and ask whose hairpin this is.

193
00:13:43,842 --> 00:13:45,144
Let's catch the culprit together.

194
00:13:45,577 --> 00:13:47,146
You stayed up all night trying
to catch the culprit, right?

195
00:13:47,146 --> 00:13:47,980
Let's do it together.

196
00:13:50,749 --> 00:13:51,583
This hairpin...

197
00:13:52,451 --> 00:13:53,952
I wasn't the one who found it.

198
00:13:54,553 --> 00:13:55,487
What?

199
00:13:56,689 --> 00:13:57,690
The manager.

200
00:13:58,624 --> 00:14:02,194
That so-called manager of the field
was running away with this in his hand,

201
00:14:02,728 --> 00:14:04,196
and I caught him.

202
00:14:04,196 --> 00:14:06,865
If you caught him running away,
shouldn't he be the first suspect?

203
00:14:08,934 --> 00:14:11,136
You said you don't want to believe
the culprit is someone...

204
00:14:11,136 --> 00:14:12,438
from Yeonri-ri, right?

205
00:14:13,539 --> 00:14:14,907
The same goes for me.

206
00:14:15,441 --> 00:14:17,009
Starting with me coming here,

207
00:14:17,843 --> 00:14:19,878
I don't want to believe that...

208
00:14:19,878 --> 00:14:21,814
all of this is Mat Story
trying to push me out.

209
00:14:31,957 --> 00:14:33,592
Promise me something.

210
00:14:34,093 --> 00:14:35,594
Let's say we catch the culprit,

211
00:14:35,594 --> 00:14:37,062
and it's not someone from Yeonri-ri.

212
00:14:37,963 --> 00:14:41,533
Then drop everything, your research
and all, and go back to Seoul.

213
00:14:44,203 --> 00:14:45,738
And what if it's someone from Yeonri-ri?

214
00:14:46,605 --> 00:14:48,574
Then I'll take responsibility
and step down as village chief.

215
00:15:18,570 --> 00:15:19,772
Bo Mi, you're crying.

216
00:15:20,005 --> 00:15:21,707
You're crying too, Ji Cheon.

217
00:15:21,707 --> 00:15:22,674
My goodness.

218
00:15:25,210 --> 00:15:27,946
Why are these onions so spicy today?

219
00:15:29,181 --> 00:15:31,517
Whose onions are these today, Bo Mi?

220
00:15:34,453 --> 00:15:36,889
Hey.

221
00:15:36,889 --> 00:15:39,625
What are you two doing
in this sacred school?

222
00:15:44,530 --> 00:15:46,632
I'm fine. It just barely grazed my finger.

223
00:15:47,332 --> 00:15:48,567
You're bleeding.

224
00:15:48,934 --> 00:15:50,636
Come on. Let's get it treated quickly.

225
00:15:50,636 --> 00:15:52,471
We'll step out to the nutrition room
for a bit.

226
00:15:52,471 --> 00:15:53,772
I'm really fine.

227
00:15:53,772 --> 00:15:55,374
I can just wash it with water.

228
00:15:56,542 --> 00:15:59,344
Unbelievable.

229
00:15:59,611 --> 00:16:01,547
This is ridiculous.

230
00:16:01,547 --> 00:16:03,649
Why don't you operate on it too?

231
00:16:06,952 --> 00:16:09,755
(Nutrition Room)

232
00:16:14,026 --> 00:16:14,893
It'll sting a bit.

233
00:16:31,777 --> 00:16:32,611
Why?

234
00:16:33,712 --> 00:16:34,680
It's too tight.

235
00:16:35,414 --> 00:16:37,449
Really? Let me fix it for you.

236
00:16:40,185 --> 00:16:43,122
Honestly, you don't have to go
this far for this.

237
00:16:46,125 --> 00:16:47,493
If it gets infected, it could scar.

238
00:16:47,493 --> 00:16:48,761
Then that'd be upsetting.

239
00:16:49,261 --> 00:16:50,929
If something this small left scars,

240
00:16:50,929 --> 00:16:52,931
I wouldn't have a finger without one.

241
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,335
I'd rather be the one getting hurt.

242
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:02,674
Let me try it.

243
00:17:03,876 --> 00:17:05,944
Try what?

244
00:17:08,147 --> 00:17:09,048
Using the knife.

245
00:17:11,984 --> 00:17:15,187
(Cafeteria)

246
00:17:24,363 --> 00:17:25,431
Seong Ji Cheon.

247
00:17:25,998 --> 00:17:27,299
Are you sure you can do this?

248
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,469
I should do it since I know how.

249
00:17:32,071 --> 00:17:33,105
I can't keep...

250
00:17:34,239 --> 00:17:35,774
avoiding it forever.

251
00:17:38,777 --> 00:17:39,778
Then don't be scared.

252
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:42,614
Are you ready?

253
00:17:43,649 --> 00:17:45,484
Yes. Let's begin.

254
00:18:10,409 --> 00:18:12,644
You have too much tension in your wrist.

255
00:18:12,644 --> 00:18:14,580
Try relaxing a bit and do it again.

256
00:18:14,580 --> 00:18:15,414
Okay.

257
00:18:23,489 --> 00:18:24,356
Much better, right?

258
00:18:29,762 --> 00:18:30,829
You're good.

259
00:18:33,365 --> 00:18:35,968
(Cafe Sunny)

260
00:18:37,503 --> 00:18:39,104
Milk...

261
00:18:39,905 --> 00:18:42,674
Four milks.

262
00:18:47,413 --> 00:18:50,082
Two sugars.

263
00:18:50,682 --> 00:18:51,750
Tea...

264
00:19:02,795 --> 00:19:04,229
- Hye Sun.
- Yes?

265
00:19:04,229 --> 00:19:06,465
I'm just going to step out for a bit.

266
00:19:06,465 --> 00:19:07,566
Okay.

267
00:19:07,933 --> 00:19:11,070
Just be back before the appointment
at the salon later.

268
00:19:11,070 --> 00:19:12,504
Okay.

269
00:19:12,504 --> 00:19:13,439
Bye.

270
00:19:19,044 --> 00:19:22,014
An almond cookie.

271
00:19:22,915 --> 00:19:25,184
A berry macaron.

272
00:19:25,184 --> 00:19:26,318
(Items Lee Seon Ja stole)

273
00:19:26,318 --> 00:19:27,786
Seon Ja.

274
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:30,255
You still live young, don't you?

275
00:19:31,590 --> 00:19:34,827
Did you think I wouldn't notice you
taking stuff from my cafe?

276
00:19:37,596 --> 00:19:39,665
This girl...

277
00:19:40,165 --> 00:19:42,267
Something's definitely going on.

278
00:19:43,268 --> 00:19:44,670
(Wang Dong Hardware)

279
00:19:44,670 --> 00:19:47,373
(Be right back)

280
00:19:52,878 --> 00:19:53,879
It's sweet.

281
00:19:56,615 --> 00:19:57,883
I'm not in right now.

282
00:19:59,318 --> 00:20:00,252
False alarm.

283
00:20:03,889 --> 00:20:04,990
You scared me.

284
00:20:04,990 --> 00:20:05,858
That hurt.

285
00:20:09,061 --> 00:20:11,463
I shouldn't be eating stuff like this.

286
00:20:11,463 --> 00:20:13,265
I need to lose weight.

287
00:20:13,265 --> 00:20:14,566
What do you mean?

288
00:20:15,734 --> 00:20:17,669
You shouldn't lose even half a pound.

289
00:20:18,203 --> 00:20:19,638
How can you say that?

290
00:20:22,207 --> 00:20:23,175
Another half a pound.

291
00:20:29,615 --> 00:20:30,449
You too, Seon Ja.

292
00:20:31,617 --> 00:20:33,252
Another half a pound.

293
00:20:34,186 --> 00:20:35,621
Not that.

294
00:20:40,959 --> 00:20:41,894
I'm really curious...

295
00:20:43,228 --> 00:20:44,830
to find out what you want.

296
00:20:54,139 --> 00:20:55,474
Where are you going?

297
00:20:59,111 --> 00:21:00,179
- It's hot.
- It's hot.

298
00:21:06,352 --> 00:21:07,186
Okay.

299
00:21:13,392 --> 00:21:14,226
Bye.

300
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:15,994
Bye.

301
00:21:25,270 --> 00:21:26,238
Who's that?

302
00:21:26,872 --> 00:21:27,940
Cho Mi Ryeo?

303
00:21:28,674 --> 00:21:30,743
Why is she acting like that?

304
00:21:30,743 --> 00:21:31,844
Is she doing something wrong?

305
00:21:32,878 --> 00:21:34,613
What's she doing?

306
00:21:35,147 --> 00:21:37,616
Why does she keep turning her head
around like that?

307
00:21:39,685 --> 00:21:40,786
Something feels off.

308
00:21:46,225 --> 00:21:49,061
I told her we have customers
at the salon today.

309
00:21:50,229 --> 00:21:51,964
Seon Ja.

310
00:21:52,297 --> 00:21:55,367
Who are you fooling around with
that you've lost your mind?

311
00:21:55,367 --> 00:21:58,237
Lee Seon Ja!

312
00:21:59,004 --> 00:22:00,606
Unbelievable.

313
00:22:02,541 --> 00:22:03,942
Goodness.

314
00:22:07,179 --> 00:22:09,348
Hello, Ms. Nam.

315
00:22:10,049 --> 00:22:11,383
So...

316
00:22:11,383 --> 00:22:15,688
I heard there's a jewelry shop
around here,

317
00:22:15,688 --> 00:22:17,389
but I can't seem to find it.

318
00:22:17,389 --> 00:22:18,257
Who told you that?

319
00:22:18,957 --> 00:22:20,526
It closed down ages ago.

320
00:22:22,027 --> 00:22:24,029
Really?

321
00:22:24,029 --> 00:22:26,699
But it shows up on the map app.

322
00:22:30,903 --> 00:22:31,737
Why?

323
00:22:38,143 --> 00:22:39,011
Never mind.

324
00:22:39,445 --> 00:22:42,381
It's been gone for a long time.

325
00:22:43,082 --> 00:22:45,117
Okay.

326
00:22:51,090 --> 00:22:52,991
The school bus is acting up again.

327
00:22:52,991 --> 00:22:55,294
Should I tell your kids
to take the village bus?

328
00:22:56,662 --> 00:23:00,099
No, I'll go pick them up.

329
00:23:03,335 --> 00:23:04,169
Goodbye.

330
00:23:05,738 --> 00:23:07,139
Bye.

331
00:23:13,712 --> 00:23:14,646
What was that about?

332
00:23:17,015 --> 00:23:17,983
Goodness.

333
00:23:17,983 --> 00:23:19,918
Forget it.

334
00:23:24,356 --> 00:23:25,924
Didn't I tell you to come back soon?

335
00:23:25,924 --> 00:23:27,493
Because we have customers in the salon?

336
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:28,927
I'm sorry.

337
00:23:29,661 --> 00:23:32,131
Hye Sun. I really did try to come early.

338
00:23:32,131 --> 00:23:33,832
I need to know now.

339
00:23:33,832 --> 00:23:35,601
Who is this guy that's keeping
your mind occupied?

340
00:23:35,601 --> 00:23:38,704
Otherwise, there's no way
I can forgive you for being late.

341
00:23:40,005 --> 00:23:42,775
What are you talking about?
I'm sick of men.

342
00:23:42,775 --> 00:23:44,510
Once was enough for me.

343
00:23:46,245 --> 00:23:48,747
I saw Cho Mi Ryeo on my way here.

344
00:23:49,481 --> 00:23:52,017
She was looking around like this.

345
00:23:52,017 --> 00:23:53,385
Something seemed really off.

346
00:23:53,385 --> 00:23:55,320
Something's going to happen again.

347
00:23:56,588 --> 00:24:00,159
If she asks you to lend her money,

348
00:24:00,459 --> 00:24:01,427
just say you don't have any.

349
00:24:01,427 --> 00:24:04,363
Why? Does that family need money
or something?

350
00:24:04,363 --> 00:24:05,964
What family doesn't need money?

351
00:24:06,465 --> 00:24:09,134
Get to work. You need to make money.

352
00:24:10,703 --> 00:24:12,438
It looks like you need to make
a lot of money too.

353
00:24:14,673 --> 00:24:15,507
What was that?

354
00:24:32,191 --> 00:24:33,325
They're not trembling anymore.

355
00:24:33,892 --> 00:24:34,827
Your hands aren't trembling anymore.

356
00:24:36,295 --> 00:24:37,830
You're right.
They're not trembling anymore.

357
00:24:44,036 --> 00:24:45,904
But...

358
00:24:48,841 --> 00:24:51,243
Now something else is trembling.

359
00:24:57,616 --> 00:24:59,284
- Let's go to the playground.
- Okay.

360
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:02,921
I think everyone's out already.

361
00:25:03,722 --> 00:25:04,890
Did they go home already?

362
00:25:07,860 --> 00:25:08,827
Should I go inside?

363
00:25:14,133 --> 00:25:15,667
Ji Gu...

364
00:25:15,667 --> 00:25:17,002
He's not here.

365
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:37,256
(Cafeteria)

366
00:25:59,678 --> 00:26:00,646
Seong Ji Cheon.

367
00:26:06,385 --> 00:26:07,219
Mom.

368
00:26:08,520 --> 00:26:09,988
What are you doing here?

369
00:26:12,024 --> 00:26:12,991
So...

370
00:26:17,096 --> 00:26:19,264
You have an apron and gloves on.

371
00:26:21,433 --> 00:26:22,534
Don't tell me.

372
00:26:23,402 --> 00:26:25,270
Have you been lying to me
about going out to study,

373
00:26:25,270 --> 00:26:28,374
while you've actually been coming here
and spending time with her?

374
00:26:29,007 --> 00:26:30,175
Mother, it's not like that...

375
00:26:30,175 --> 00:26:31,143
Hold on.

376
00:26:32,911 --> 00:26:34,880
I'll hear the details from my son.

377
00:26:42,154 --> 00:26:42,988
Yes.

378
00:26:45,257 --> 00:26:47,126
I've been working here.

379
00:26:48,260 --> 00:26:49,228
Why?

380
00:26:51,864 --> 00:26:53,198
Tell me right now.

381
00:26:54,133 --> 00:26:55,334
Mom, stop.

382
00:26:55,334 --> 00:26:56,535
Why are you working here?

383
00:26:56,535 --> 00:26:57,903
Let's talk at home, okay?

384
00:26:57,903 --> 00:26:58,904
Why?

385
00:26:58,904 --> 00:27:01,106
- Stop. Let's talk at home.
- Why are you working here?

386
00:27:01,106 --> 00:27:03,208
- Let's talk at home.
- Why?

387
00:27:30,703 --> 00:27:32,571
(Patrol, neighborhood watch)

388
00:27:41,613 --> 00:27:43,515
Yeonri-ri is a crime-free village.

389
00:27:44,616 --> 00:27:46,151
I'll prove it.

390
00:27:46,151 --> 00:27:47,886
I swear on my name, Im Ju Hyeong.

391
00:27:50,756 --> 00:27:52,591
You know what an undercover stakeout
is, right?

392
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:56,462
It means to lie low...

393
00:27:56,462 --> 00:27:58,364
No, it means to go under and hide.

394
00:27:59,765 --> 00:28:02,101
If you close the door behind you,
how am I supposed to go in?

395
00:28:11,677 --> 00:28:12,544
Come on.

396
00:28:12,544 --> 00:28:13,812
Seriously. Darn.

397
00:28:13,812 --> 00:28:16,915
You're really good at swearing.

398
00:28:17,282 --> 00:28:19,118
Based on looks, I'd say
you're the culprit.

399
00:28:19,752 --> 00:28:21,787
Who are you to talk about looks?

400
00:28:21,787 --> 00:28:24,990
You look like a startled penguin
who got caught stealing food.

401
00:28:24,990 --> 00:28:26,091
Stay focused.

402
00:28:29,728 --> 00:28:31,897
Penguin? That's a new one.

403
00:28:36,135 --> 00:28:38,937
I'm suddenly hungry.

404
00:28:40,639 --> 00:28:41,874
I knew this would happen.

405
00:28:47,546 --> 00:28:48,881
I'm good.

406
00:28:53,085 --> 00:28:54,920
You're only offering once?
That's not fair.

407
00:28:59,525 --> 00:29:01,193
Ji Sang. Ji Gu.

408
00:29:01,527 --> 00:29:03,462
Did you know Ji Cheon was working
at school, too?

409
00:29:05,731 --> 00:29:06,865
I guess you did.

410
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:11,804
The three of you love each other
very much.

411
00:29:11,804 --> 00:29:14,440
Did you enjoy lying to me together?

412
00:29:15,808 --> 00:29:17,042
You got caught again?

413
00:29:17,042 --> 00:29:19,344
How did you even get into med school
with that brain of yours?

414
00:29:19,344 --> 00:29:20,779
Did you lie just to get caught?

415
00:29:20,779 --> 00:29:21,714
Seong Ji Sang.

416
00:29:22,014 --> 00:29:24,316
If you have something to say,
say it loud and clear.

417
00:29:26,251 --> 00:29:28,287
Mom, this is between you and me.

418
00:29:28,754 --> 00:29:29,655
You two can go to your room.

419
00:29:30,456 --> 00:29:31,290
Okay.

420
00:29:31,623 --> 00:29:32,458
Let's go.

421
00:29:33,659 --> 00:29:34,626
Go.

422
00:29:36,862 --> 00:29:37,730
Fine.

423
00:29:38,664 --> 00:29:40,265
Let's hear it.

424
00:29:40,899 --> 00:29:43,902
What were you doing there?
Being so close to that girl.

425
00:29:44,370 --> 00:29:46,038
Is this really the time for that?

426
00:30:04,223 --> 00:30:05,157
Mother.

427
00:30:09,661 --> 00:30:11,063
I have something to tell you.

428
00:30:13,399 --> 00:30:15,267
Honestly, even now,
it's already very late.

429
00:30:16,235 --> 00:30:18,003
It's not true, is it?

430
00:30:19,071 --> 00:30:20,839
Tell me it's not true.

431
00:30:23,909 --> 00:30:25,444
What you're thinking is right.

432
00:30:28,247 --> 00:30:29,281
You see...

433
00:30:32,084 --> 00:30:33,652
To tell you the truth, I...

434
00:30:33,652 --> 00:30:34,553
You...

435
00:30:36,922 --> 00:30:38,857
You...

436
00:30:38,857 --> 00:30:39,692
A child?

437
00:30:41,060 --> 00:30:42,995
Is she pregnant?

438
00:30:42,995 --> 00:30:44,997
What are you talking about? Mom.

439
00:30:45,531 --> 00:30:46,432
You punk!

440
00:30:48,734 --> 00:30:51,437
You!

441
00:30:51,870 --> 00:30:54,006
If you're going to date someone,

442
00:30:54,006 --> 00:30:55,607
you should meet someone from med school.

443
00:30:55,607 --> 00:30:56,742
Why date someone from here?

444
00:30:56,742 --> 00:30:58,544
- Are you going to settle down here?
- That's not it.

445
00:30:58,544 --> 00:30:59,812
Hear me out.

446
00:30:59,812 --> 00:31:02,414
Go to your room and study.

447
00:31:02,414 --> 00:31:03,549
How dare you.

448
00:31:16,929 --> 00:31:18,564
You were sound asleep.

449
00:31:19,998 --> 00:31:20,933
Who was?

450
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:23,535
Sleep some more. I can do this by myself.

451
00:31:24,303 --> 00:31:27,139
At least wipe the drool off your mouth
before you talk.

452
00:31:27,139 --> 00:31:29,007
By the way, why do you keep
talking casually to me?

453
00:31:30,142 --> 00:31:31,276
You can do it too.

454
00:31:33,679 --> 00:31:37,249
Okay. By the way, I may look young,

455
00:31:37,883 --> 00:31:39,385
but I'm sure I'm older than you.

456
00:31:40,586 --> 00:31:42,955
Do you even know how to write
undercover stakeout in Chinese?

457
00:31:43,856 --> 00:31:45,457
I can write it in English.

458
00:31:45,758 --> 00:31:46,725
Do it.

459
00:31:47,359 --> 00:31:48,427
Undercover.

460
00:31:48,861 --> 00:31:50,796
I said to write it, so spell it out.

461
00:31:51,163 --> 00:31:52,865
Un...

462
00:31:55,734 --> 00:31:56,869
Did you hear that?

463
00:31:57,870 --> 00:31:58,937
Hear what?

464
00:31:59,538 --> 00:32:02,541
Didn't you hear a woman crying?

465
00:32:22,361 --> 00:32:23,629
Isn't that a person?

466
00:32:25,564 --> 00:32:26,965
Shouldn't we go check?

467
00:32:34,039 --> 00:32:35,407
Don't make any noise.

468
00:32:40,779 --> 00:32:42,281
I didn't make any noise.

469
00:32:47,586 --> 00:32:49,788
Let's be thoroughly prepared...

470
00:32:49,788 --> 00:32:51,757
and go out to check.

471
00:32:51,757 --> 00:32:52,524
Okay.

472
00:32:53,058 --> 00:32:53,926
Let's go.

473
00:32:54,493 --> 00:32:56,228
- Go first.
- By the way...

474
00:32:56,962 --> 00:32:59,465
This is your field,
so shouldn't you go first?

475
00:33:00,265 --> 00:33:02,234
You're the village chief.

476
00:33:02,234 --> 00:33:05,170
You should be the one protecting everyone.

477
00:33:05,170 --> 00:33:07,239
You go first.

478
00:33:11,577 --> 00:33:12,845
Now, you go first.

479
00:33:34,933 --> 00:33:36,869
Must I step down even if
it's a Yeonri-ri ghost?

480
00:33:36,869 --> 00:33:39,338
There are no ghosts.

481
00:33:39,338 --> 00:33:40,739
Is that right? Then you go first.

482
00:33:40,739 --> 00:33:42,007
Come on. Let's go together.

483
00:33:42,007 --> 00:33:43,509
- No, you go first.
- Let's go together.

484
00:33:43,509 --> 00:33:44,710
You're a big guy.

485
00:33:44,710 --> 00:33:46,945
So big guys aren't afraid of ghosts?

486
00:33:46,945 --> 00:33:48,714
People in the countryside...

487
00:33:55,788 --> 00:33:56,655
It's empty.

488
00:33:57,256 --> 00:33:59,925
I told you. It's a ghost.

489
00:34:06,899 --> 00:34:07,800
Help me!

490
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:09,401
A ghost.

491
00:34:09,401 --> 00:34:11,570
Please help me.

492
00:34:11,570 --> 00:34:13,005
You traitor.

493
00:34:18,343 --> 00:34:20,279
Have you seen Mak Dung?

494
00:34:22,214 --> 00:34:24,183
Mak Rae?

495
00:34:25,851 --> 00:34:26,785
I...

496
00:34:28,087 --> 00:34:30,089
told him to wait right here.

497
00:34:32,391 --> 00:34:34,593
Where did Mak Dung go?

498
00:34:35,394 --> 00:34:36,895
Mak Dung?

499
00:34:36,895 --> 00:34:38,097
My youngest.

500
00:34:51,810 --> 00:34:54,346
Over there.

501
00:34:55,414 --> 00:34:58,217
We need to go look over there.

502
00:35:00,652 --> 00:35:03,756
Don't worry, Mak Rae.
We'll find him for you.

503
00:35:03,756 --> 00:35:07,359
My baby must be freezing.

504
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:11,497
I need to find him quickly.

505
00:35:11,997 --> 00:35:13,032
Mak Dung.

506
00:35:13,032 --> 00:35:14,166
Let's go home.

507
00:35:31,483 --> 00:35:32,384
Thanks for your help.

508
00:35:35,354 --> 00:35:36,622
Are you okay?

509
00:35:43,362 --> 00:35:44,830
Mak Rae.

510
00:35:44,830 --> 00:35:46,498
Where are you?

511
00:35:46,498 --> 00:35:47,633
Mak Rae.

512
00:35:47,633 --> 00:35:49,601
Mak Rae.

513
00:35:50,869 --> 00:35:52,604
Are you okay?

514
00:35:53,605 --> 00:35:55,507
Goodness.

515
00:35:55,507 --> 00:35:58,877
Why did you go there barefoot?

516
00:35:59,778 --> 00:36:01,914
Mak Dung.

517
00:36:03,015 --> 00:36:04,249
To find his clothes.

518
00:36:09,021 --> 00:36:10,222
My goodness.

519
00:36:14,693 --> 00:36:15,894
We...

520
00:36:17,096 --> 00:36:19,064
should've burned those clothes back then.

521
00:36:22,301 --> 00:36:25,838
Instead of burning the thing
that was lighting a fire in her heart,

522
00:36:25,838 --> 00:36:30,542
we just buried them in the ground.
That's why this happened.

523
00:36:31,610 --> 00:36:32,678
It's all my fault.

524
00:36:34,413 --> 00:36:35,381
It's all my fault.

525
00:36:38,050 --> 00:36:40,185
It's my fault, Mak Rae.

526
00:36:41,620 --> 00:36:44,556
I'm sorry. What are we going to do?

527
00:36:44,556 --> 00:36:45,324
That's enough.

528
00:36:45,324 --> 00:36:47,026
I'm sorry.

529
00:36:47,026 --> 00:36:48,694
That's enough.

530
00:36:49,461 --> 00:36:51,764
It's no one's fault.

531
00:36:52,998 --> 00:36:53,832
That's enough.

532
00:36:54,166 --> 00:36:55,934
I'm sorry, Mak Rae.

533
00:37:09,081 --> 00:37:11,684
I'll get going now.

534
00:37:11,684 --> 00:37:12,918
I'll come by your house tomorrow.

535
00:37:14,420 --> 00:37:15,454
Mak Dung.

536
00:37:16,288 --> 00:37:17,523
Where are you going?

537
00:37:17,856 --> 00:37:20,626
It's late. You should stay the night.

538
00:37:21,326 --> 00:37:23,529
It's dark out. Where do you think
you're going?

539
00:37:23,529 --> 00:37:24,963
Come here.

540
00:37:24,963 --> 00:37:26,999
- Stay the night.
- What?

541
00:37:26,999 --> 00:37:28,867
Come here. Stay the night.

542
00:37:28,867 --> 00:37:30,369
- Come here.
- But I...

543
00:37:31,236 --> 00:37:32,705
Stay the night.

544
00:37:32,705 --> 00:37:33,739
Come here.

545
00:37:34,039 --> 00:37:35,741
Mak Dung, come here.

546
00:37:47,653 --> 00:37:49,221
You must've been shocked.

547
00:37:50,489 --> 00:37:51,657
I'm sorry.

548
00:37:52,257 --> 00:37:53,759
No, it's okay.

549
00:38:01,367 --> 00:38:02,568
Mak Dung...

550
00:38:07,473 --> 00:38:09,575
is her youngest child she lost.

551
00:38:11,043 --> 00:38:12,578
For days,

552
00:38:14,246 --> 00:38:15,681
she couldn't even eat.

553
00:38:17,616 --> 00:38:20,919
She held onto his clothes and cried...

554
00:38:21,787 --> 00:38:24,223
for days.

555
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:32,364
We were afraid we'd lose Mak Rae too,

556
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,869
so we took the child's clothes...

557
00:38:39,071 --> 00:38:42,307
and buried them up there.

558
00:38:50,282 --> 00:38:52,518
Mak Dung, my baby.

559
00:38:55,854 --> 00:38:56,889
Mak Dung.

560
00:38:58,157 --> 00:38:59,358
Your clothes...

561
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:02,261
You must be cold.

562
00:39:03,195 --> 00:39:05,497
I must find your clothes quickly...

563
00:39:06,565 --> 00:39:08,267
and put them on you.

564
00:39:09,902 --> 00:39:12,137
Mak Dung, my baby.

565
00:39:13,505 --> 00:39:14,673
Let's find them.

566
00:39:17,609 --> 00:39:19,511
Mak Dung. I'm sure it's here somewhere.

567
00:39:19,511 --> 00:39:21,747
We thought she had gotten over it
and was doing okay.

568
00:39:23,048 --> 00:39:24,183
But I guess it's still buried deep inside.

569
00:39:25,884 --> 00:39:28,987
It's been buried so deep in her heart.

570
00:39:30,689 --> 00:39:32,725
I'll find them and put them on you.

571
00:39:38,530 --> 00:39:42,034
I'm so sorry, Mak Rae.

572
00:39:42,968 --> 00:39:46,705
I did it because I was afraid
that you'd be too heartbroken.

573
00:39:49,108 --> 00:39:51,610
Your insides must've been
burning up inside.

574
00:39:56,682 --> 00:40:00,185
I should've noticed it...

575
00:40:00,519 --> 00:40:02,287
when Mak Rae mentioned Mak Dung...

576
00:40:04,056 --> 00:40:06,125
at the cafe the other day.

577
00:40:06,125 --> 00:40:06,992
Goodness.

578
00:40:07,793 --> 00:40:09,928
Even I didn't notice,
living under the same roof.

579
00:40:09,928 --> 00:40:12,164
How could you have known?

580
00:40:14,633 --> 00:40:15,567
Once in a while,

581
00:40:17,770 --> 00:40:20,105
she would act like that out of nowhere.

582
00:40:20,105 --> 00:40:22,541
I did feel like something was a bit off.

583
00:40:26,078 --> 00:40:28,147
I guess I just wanted to believe
it wasn't true.

584
00:40:32,251 --> 00:40:33,519
I'm here.

585
00:40:35,954 --> 00:40:37,423
Just in case,

586
00:40:37,956 --> 00:40:40,959
I brought some calming pills
and herbal tonic.

587
00:40:42,995 --> 00:40:44,129
Is she all right?

588
00:40:52,104 --> 00:40:53,806
Dong Sik, bring another towel.

589
00:40:53,806 --> 00:40:55,107
Her feet are still cold.

590
00:40:55,107 --> 00:40:57,609
Yes, the heating will kick in soon too.

591
00:40:57,943 --> 00:41:00,279
Bo Mi, lay down another blanket here.

592
00:41:00,779 --> 00:41:03,716
You should all stay here
and sleep tonight.

593
00:41:17,996 --> 00:41:19,832
People who aren't even related by blood...

594
00:41:23,869 --> 00:41:25,437
still know where each other hurts,

595
00:41:28,240 --> 00:41:31,744
what burdens they carry in their hearts...

596
00:41:34,012 --> 00:41:35,280
and gather like this tonight.

597
00:41:52,598 --> 00:41:53,699
Well...

598
00:41:56,301 --> 00:41:57,503
About the damaged field...

599
00:41:58,837 --> 00:42:01,940
- I'll compensate for it...
- It's okay.

600
00:42:03,409 --> 00:42:04,309
Why?

601
00:42:05,244 --> 00:42:06,412
Doesn't this mean you won?

602
00:42:07,413 --> 00:42:09,715
If you want, I can even step down
as village chief.

603
00:42:11,316 --> 00:42:12,384
No.

604
00:42:14,353 --> 00:42:16,255
She didn't do it on purpose.

605
00:42:17,356 --> 00:42:20,526
Honestly, I don't know if it's okay
for me to walk away like this.

606
00:42:26,865 --> 00:42:28,567
The soil in Yeonri-ri is heavy.

607
00:42:30,536 --> 00:42:31,937
Your feet sink deep into it.

608
00:42:32,838 --> 00:42:34,873
Even if you shake it off, it clings again.

609
00:42:36,308 --> 00:42:37,643
But a field...

610
00:42:38,077 --> 00:42:40,145
If you plant something,
somehow, it will grow.

611
00:42:42,448 --> 00:42:43,982
Even when you think it's dead,

612
00:42:43,982 --> 00:42:46,452
when spring comes, it sprouts again.

613
00:42:55,828 --> 00:42:56,729
I'll get going.

614
00:42:59,231 --> 00:43:00,132
Seong Tae Hun.

615
00:43:05,904 --> 00:43:07,106
Didn't we agree to drop the formalities?

616
00:43:19,818 --> 00:43:20,786
I was born in 1975.

617
00:43:23,389 --> 00:43:24,590
I was born in early 1976.

618
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:26,191
Then...

619
00:43:27,359 --> 00:43:28,260
we're basically friends.

620
00:43:30,329 --> 00:43:31,263
Bye.

621
00:43:43,308 --> 00:43:46,378
The person you're trying to reach
is unavailable.

622
00:43:47,112 --> 00:43:49,081
Seriously, Seong Tae Hun?

623
00:43:49,581 --> 00:43:51,150
Is cabbage the only thing
that matters to you?

624
00:43:51,483 --> 00:43:54,553
Your kid's life is about to fall apart.

625
00:44:08,333 --> 00:44:09,435
Let's...

626
00:44:10,436 --> 00:44:11,770
be honest with Mom too.

627
00:44:14,606 --> 00:44:15,674
You're still young.

628
00:44:16,475 --> 00:44:18,110
It's not too late, Seong Ji Cheon.

629
00:44:19,278 --> 00:44:20,713
Maybe you're not hiding.

630
00:44:21,380 --> 00:44:22,681
Maybe you're actually moving forward...

631
00:44:24,583 --> 00:44:27,786
toward a path that truly suits you.

632
00:44:28,787 --> 00:44:29,955
Slowly, at your own pace.

633
00:44:34,760 --> 00:44:36,628
I'm finding my way onto the right path.

634
00:44:38,464 --> 00:44:40,699
I'll prove it with results.

635
00:45:03,255 --> 00:45:04,423
You're still up?

636
00:45:07,259 --> 00:45:08,694
Is your phone just for decoration?

637
00:45:12,664 --> 00:45:14,400
You called.

638
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:15,834
I'm sorry. I didn't see it.

639
00:45:17,236 --> 00:45:18,937
Did something happen?

640
00:45:21,507 --> 00:45:24,343
Cabbage is the only thing
on your mind, isn't it?

641
00:45:25,611 --> 00:45:27,746
I'm the only one thinking
about the kids, right?

642
00:45:29,081 --> 00:45:32,551
Why would you say something like that?

643
00:45:33,018 --> 00:45:33,919
Am I wrong?

644
00:45:35,254 --> 00:45:38,924
Even in Canada, I handled parenting
and their education all by myself.

645
00:45:38,924 --> 00:45:41,193
And here too, I'm the only one
thinking about them.

646
00:45:41,994 --> 00:45:43,829
Did Ji Sang get into trouble again?

647
00:45:48,100 --> 00:45:49,068
Seong Ji Cheon.

648
00:45:57,543 --> 00:45:58,377
What?

649
00:46:00,112 --> 00:46:01,380
You knew?

650
00:46:02,281 --> 00:46:04,583
About what?

651
00:46:07,152 --> 00:46:09,088
You did know.

652
00:46:10,456 --> 00:46:11,857
Since when?

653
00:46:12,925 --> 00:46:15,794
I only found out recently.

654
00:46:15,794 --> 00:46:17,830
I wasn't trying to hide it from you.

655
00:46:17,830 --> 00:46:19,732
I just wanted to give Ji Cheon some time.

656
00:46:19,732 --> 00:46:21,133
That is hiding it.

657
00:46:21,133 --> 00:46:24,069
How could you not tell me
something like that about Ji Cheon?

658
00:46:24,370 --> 00:46:26,872
I did it for you. I'm sorry.

659
00:46:26,872 --> 00:46:29,508
But Ji Cheon is a thoughtful kid.
You know that.

660
00:46:30,109 --> 00:46:32,144
Even so, he's still just a kid.

661
00:46:32,745 --> 00:46:36,081
It's our job as parents to shorten
the time they spend lost.

662
00:46:36,081 --> 00:46:37,516
You didn't know that?

663
00:46:37,983 --> 00:46:40,819
Do you want him to get stuck
in this countryside?

664
00:46:41,620 --> 00:46:42,921
Well...

665
00:46:44,023 --> 00:46:45,624
Honey.

666
00:46:46,525 --> 00:46:49,061
Dropping out of med school
doesn't mean his life is over.

667
00:46:50,162 --> 00:46:50,996
What?

668
00:46:52,064 --> 00:46:53,332
He did what?

669
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:55,734
You...

670
00:46:56,568 --> 00:46:58,537
weren't talking about him
dropping out of med school?

671
00:46:59,872 --> 00:47:00,939
Dropped out?

672
00:47:02,908 --> 00:47:04,443
He dropped out of med school?

673
00:47:07,479 --> 00:47:09,681
- Seong Ji Cheon, come out here!
- Calm down, honey.

674
00:47:09,681 --> 00:47:11,417
- Seong Ji Cheon.
- Calm down.

675
00:47:11,417 --> 00:47:12,918
- Let go of me.
- Calm down, honey.

676
00:47:12,918 --> 00:47:14,186
- Seong Ji Cheon.
- Calm down, honey.

677
00:47:14,186 --> 00:47:15,320
- Let go of me.
- Honey, please.

678
00:47:15,320 --> 00:47:17,423
Let's talk this out.

679
00:47:17,423 --> 00:47:19,291
- Seong Ji Cheon.
- Calm down.

680
00:47:19,291 --> 00:47:20,926
- Let go.
- Calm down.

681
00:47:22,695 --> 00:47:26,365
You didn't quit school, right?

682
00:47:26,365 --> 00:47:27,599
Dad misunderstood, right?

683
00:47:31,737 --> 00:47:32,838
I did drop out.

684
00:47:36,041 --> 00:47:37,176
I'll explain everything.

685
00:47:38,343 --> 00:47:39,311
You...

686
00:47:40,012 --> 00:47:42,181
How can you do this to me?

687
00:47:42,181 --> 00:47:43,549
- Do you know...
- Honey.

688
00:47:43,549 --> 00:47:44,783
- because of whom...
- Honey.

689
00:47:44,783 --> 00:47:46,218
Calm down, honey.

690
00:47:46,218 --> 00:47:48,587
- I endured everything?
- Calm down.

691
00:47:48,587 --> 00:47:49,922
How could you...

692
00:47:49,922 --> 00:47:51,824
Apologize to Mom, Ji Cheon.

693
00:47:51,824 --> 00:47:52,691
Calm down, honey.

694
00:47:52,691 --> 00:47:56,128
- Do you know who's keeping me alive?
- Calm down, honey.

695
00:47:56,128 --> 00:47:58,430
- Do you know who's keeping me alive?
- Honey.

696
00:48:03,001 --> 00:48:04,770
Honey.

697
00:48:05,304 --> 00:48:07,005
What's wrong?

698
00:48:08,874 --> 00:48:11,009
Honey, what's wrong?

699
00:48:11,009 --> 00:48:13,712
Honey.

700
00:48:15,114 --> 00:48:17,683
What's wrong? Wake up.

701
00:48:17,983 --> 00:48:19,918
- What's wrong, honey?
- Mom.

702
00:48:19,918 --> 00:48:22,054
- What's wrong?
- Mom.

703
00:48:22,054 --> 00:48:23,188
Look at me. Open your eyes.

704
00:48:23,188 --> 00:48:25,324
- Mom, look at me.
- Wake up, honey.

705
00:48:25,324 --> 00:48:27,526
- Breathe.
- Honey.

706
00:48:28,160 --> 00:48:29,962
- Under the sink.
- Under the sink?

707
00:48:29,962 --> 00:48:30,996
Under the sink.

708
00:48:32,031 --> 00:48:33,899
No, it's just sleeping pills.

709
00:48:33,899 --> 00:48:35,534
Just sometimes...

710
00:48:35,534 --> 00:48:36,668
It's not anything strong.

711
00:48:36,668 --> 00:48:38,637
I occasionally take one
when I can't sleep.

712
00:48:39,271 --> 00:48:41,907
- Under the sink.
- Under the sink. Her pills.

713
00:48:41,907 --> 00:48:43,175
- Mom, breathe.
- The pills.

714
00:48:44,743 --> 00:48:45,778
Under the sink.

715
00:48:49,314 --> 00:48:51,016
Honey, hold on.

716
00:48:51,016 --> 00:48:52,317
Mom.

717
00:48:52,317 --> 00:48:53,819
Breathe, Mom.

718
00:48:59,091 --> 00:49:00,359
Honey, here's water.

719
00:49:00,359 --> 00:49:03,028
This is medication for panic disorder.

720
00:49:04,163 --> 00:49:06,365
Panic disorder?

721
00:49:06,899 --> 00:49:08,667
Since when, honey?

722
00:49:09,168 --> 00:49:10,169
Honey.

723
00:49:10,169 --> 00:49:12,204
Are you okay, honey?

724
00:49:12,204 --> 00:49:14,707
Are you okay, honey?

725
00:49:14,707 --> 00:49:15,708
I'm sorry.

726
00:49:16,975 --> 00:49:18,110
I'm sorry, Mom.

727
00:49:21,880 --> 00:49:23,382
Mom will be okay.

728
00:49:24,083 --> 00:49:25,150
Under the same roof,

729
00:49:26,018 --> 00:49:28,921
I thought there was nothing
I didn't know.

730
00:49:30,689 --> 00:49:33,992
When even I was hiding things
from my own family...

731
00:49:39,932 --> 00:49:40,833
What if...

732
00:49:42,368 --> 00:49:44,036
it's already too late?

733
00:49:46,605 --> 00:49:47,439
What if...

734
00:49:48,574 --> 00:49:50,409
this is something...

735
00:49:52,211 --> 00:49:53,078
that can't be fixed anymore?

736
00:49:53,078 --> 00:49:54,079
Wake up, honey.

737
00:51:41,186 --> 00:51:43,655
(Simwoo-myeon, Yeonri-ri)

738
00:52:09,348 --> 00:52:10,783
(Three years in Mat Story's New Business)

739
00:52:10,783 --> 00:52:12,151
(Changes led by Manager Seong Tae Hun)

740
00:52:12,151 --> 00:52:13,452
(Employee Records)

741
00:52:17,022 --> 00:52:18,257
(Performance Evaluation Forms)

742
00:52:31,904 --> 00:52:32,838
Yes?

743
00:52:32,838 --> 00:52:33,972
Hey, Mr. Noh.

744
00:52:34,740 --> 00:52:36,208
You must be very busy.

745
00:52:36,508 --> 00:52:37,342
Well...

746
00:52:38,343 --> 00:52:40,512
I was planning to observe a bit longer.

747
00:52:41,447 --> 00:52:43,882
Observe what?

748
00:52:44,316 --> 00:52:46,285
You think I put you there
just to sit and watch?

749
00:52:47,486 --> 00:52:48,387
Mr. Noh.

750
00:52:48,754 --> 00:52:51,790
Did you forget the past already
just because it's been over ten years?

751
00:52:52,691 --> 00:52:55,861
I made you into someone
when you were practically dead.

752
00:52:56,729 --> 00:52:58,397
So do as you're told.

753
00:52:58,831 --> 00:53:00,699
I'll make the decisions
since I'm the smart one here.

754
00:53:22,521 --> 00:53:23,489
Are you in there?

755
00:53:43,108 --> 00:53:44,476
What brings you all here so early?

756
00:54:00,659 --> 00:54:04,496
We're already done harvesting.

757
00:54:05,330 --> 00:54:07,800
If you're not going to quit this research,

758
00:54:08,801 --> 00:54:10,602
it's way better to grow them indoors.

759
00:54:10,602 --> 00:54:11,870
No risk of frost either.

760
00:54:12,371 --> 00:54:13,672
You must see through what you started.

761
00:54:17,376 --> 00:54:18,310
Because of this,

762
00:54:19,244 --> 00:54:21,680
you all came out here this early?

763
00:54:22,614 --> 00:54:24,316
If you've pulled the radish,
you must cut the knife.

764
00:54:24,983 --> 00:54:27,653
It's the other way around. You must
take out the knife to cut the radish.

765
00:54:28,921 --> 00:54:30,289
I don't like owing someone.

766
00:54:36,628 --> 00:54:37,963
Thank you, everyone.

767
00:54:55,848 --> 00:54:57,149
How refreshing.

768
00:54:57,149 --> 00:54:59,118
That fertilizer smell.

769
00:54:59,451 --> 00:55:00,319
Goodness.

770
00:55:01,153 --> 00:55:02,988
Seriously, what am I doing here?

771
00:55:09,228 --> 00:55:10,095
What?

772
00:55:14,566 --> 00:55:15,401
My goodness.

773
00:55:18,337 --> 00:55:19,872
No cabbage.

774
00:55:20,339 --> 00:55:23,042
No cabbage. Unbelievable.

775
00:55:24,510 --> 00:55:25,911
No cabbage.

776
00:55:26,845 --> 00:55:28,380
No cabbage.

777
00:55:30,549 --> 00:55:32,251
What brings you here without notice?

778
00:55:33,318 --> 00:55:36,055
I came because I had something urgent
to tell you.

779
00:55:46,865 --> 00:55:47,800
I'm sorry.

780
00:55:48,200 --> 00:55:50,335
It's my fault for neglecting the field.

781
00:55:51,403 --> 00:55:52,838
Not at all.

782
00:55:52,838 --> 00:55:54,506
You're doing a great job, Mr. Seong.

783
00:55:55,374 --> 00:55:56,875
You're doing more than enough...

784
00:55:57,476 --> 00:55:58,577
for Mat Story.

785
00:56:02,548 --> 00:56:06,018
Plug your noses.
The stench is overwhelming.

786
00:56:06,018 --> 00:56:08,921
Is Mat Story getting ready
to pull something again?

787
00:56:09,855 --> 00:56:13,325
Things seem pretty complicated
for Mr. Seong.

788
00:56:14,426 --> 00:56:16,195
By the way, that man...

789
00:56:17,396 --> 00:56:19,131
looks familiar.

790
00:56:19,965 --> 00:56:21,667
I've got a bad feeling about this.

791
00:56:23,268 --> 00:56:24,770
So...

792
00:56:25,337 --> 00:56:28,607
there are new instructions
from the executive director.

793
00:56:30,075 --> 00:56:31,410
Here in Yeonri-ri,

794
00:56:32,878 --> 00:56:36,315
our company's new vision will take shape.

795
00:56:37,015 --> 00:56:37,916
We want you,

796
00:56:38,884 --> 00:56:40,753
Mr. Seong, to carry it out yourself.

797
00:56:41,587 --> 00:56:44,923
With those hands that have only worked
on cabbage for Mat Story...

798
00:56:44,923 --> 00:56:47,126
In the name of Seong Tae Hun.

799
00:56:47,693 --> 00:56:50,295
Isn't that job to research
and develop cabbage?

800
00:57:03,675 --> 00:57:04,610
Unbelievable.

801
00:57:10,115 --> 00:57:10,983
Take this.

802
00:57:12,084 --> 00:57:13,218
Come on.

803
00:57:13,552 --> 00:57:14,586
What is this?

804
00:57:14,853 --> 00:57:17,890
You'll hear it directly from Mr. Bae
when you see him soon.

805
00:57:18,590 --> 00:57:19,658
Mr. Choi.

806
00:57:20,526 --> 00:57:21,927
Why did you really come here?

807
00:57:24,229 --> 00:57:26,365
I came here to work.

808
00:57:26,365 --> 00:57:27,733
Let's work.

809
00:57:29,535 --> 00:57:30,903
Let's work.

810
00:57:32,004 --> 00:57:33,906
Don't those people ever move away?

811
00:57:33,906 --> 00:57:35,140
I'm so sick of them.

812
00:57:35,140 --> 00:57:36,742
They didn't recognize me, did they?

813
00:57:36,742 --> 00:57:39,078
Move the car.

814
00:57:51,023 --> 00:57:52,858
(Analysis Report)

815
00:57:52,858 --> 00:57:54,426
(Pesticide residues)

816
00:57:54,426 --> 00:57:56,929
(chlorpyrifos, imidacloprid, fail)

817
00:58:06,839 --> 00:58:09,341
(Lead, cadmium, arsenic,
mercury, fail)

818
00:58:10,609 --> 00:58:12,711
What is this?

819
00:58:13,479 --> 00:58:14,480
What's this?

820
00:58:15,447 --> 00:58:16,548
This is ridiculous.

821
00:58:19,885 --> 00:58:21,653
"You only see as much as you know."

822
00:58:21,653 --> 00:58:23,622
That's been my philosophy as a researcher.

823
00:58:26,625 --> 00:58:28,227
I believed that everything I could see,

824
00:58:28,227 --> 00:58:29,962
I knew.

825
00:58:30,562 --> 00:58:32,097
And I thought that was all there was.

826
00:58:36,668 --> 00:58:39,538
But I didn't know anything at all.

827
00:58:44,476 --> 00:58:45,711
Not my wife's pain...

828
00:58:50,582 --> 00:58:51,850
Not my children's hearts...

829
00:58:54,720 --> 00:58:56,088
Not the true face of the company...

830
00:58:58,857 --> 00:59:00,826
(Pesticide residue- Fail)

831
00:59:00,826 --> 00:59:02,661
that I devoted my life to.

832
00:59:03,696 --> 00:59:07,266
(Fail)

833
00:59:36,428 --> 00:59:39,431
(Cabbage Your Life)

834
00:59:39,431 --> 00:59:40,899
How could this make sense?

835
00:59:40,899 --> 00:59:42,901
These numbers can't be right.

836
00:59:42,901 --> 00:59:43,969
I'll do it again.

837
00:59:43,969 --> 00:59:46,071
Your mind's been elsewhere all day.

838
00:59:46,071 --> 00:59:48,207
Please give me some time.

839
00:59:48,207 --> 00:59:52,277
Just imagining you as Dr. Seong
treating patients...

840
00:59:52,277 --> 00:59:53,879
makes me smile even in my sleep.

841
00:59:53,879 --> 00:59:56,081
Can you please stop calling me Dr. Seong?

842
00:59:56,081 --> 00:59:59,084
You need to take the board exam soon.

843
00:59:59,084 --> 01:00:01,186
I won't go back to Seoul no matter what.

844
01:00:01,186 --> 01:00:03,789
Every choice comes with responsibility.

845
01:00:03,789 --> 01:00:06,492
Did a lot of people from Mat Story
come down here before?

846
01:00:06,492 --> 01:00:08,794
There was only one person who came
as the one in charge.

847
01:00:08,794 --> 01:00:10,662
What are they up to?

848
01:00:10,996 --> 01:00:12,998
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
